<h1>Problem 1916 - 2024 ELMO, P1 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Given a convex quadrilateral \(ABCD\) where its diagonals intersect at \(E\), let \(P,Q = (ADE) \cap AB, (BEC) \cap AB\) respectively and let \(R,S = (APC) \cap AD, (BQD) \cap BC\). Prove that \(A,B,S,R\) are concyclic.</p>
<h2>Idea</h2>
<p>Take that <b>leap of faith</b>.</p>
